Preamble
This license governs the use, modification, distribution, and commercialization
of software, documentation, designs, and other materials that are part of the
Sovereign Titan Genesis (STG) ecosystem, including STG-001 through STG-012,
JASAWAN, and all affiliated modules and derivatives (collectively "STG Works").
STG is founded on principles of technological sovereignty, ethical use, and
open collaboration. This dual-license model offers a protective open-source
path and a commercial sovereign path for entities requiring commercial terms.

Definitions
1. "Licensor" means QUORUM‑STATE ‑INT'L and its assigns.
2. "Licensee" means any individual or entity exercising rights under this license.
3. "Derivative" means any work based upon the STG Works, in whole or in part.
4. "Prohibited Uses" means uses listed in Section 6.

Choice of License
The Licensee must choose one of the following license tracks before exercising
any rights granted herein:
  A. STG‑12L‑OS (Open Source Track)
  B. STG‑12L‑CS (Commercial Sovereign Track)

A. STG‑12L‑OS — Open Source Track (Copyleft, Ethical)
Grant of Rights
  The Licensor grants the Licensee a worldwide, royalty‑free, non‑exclusive,
  perpetual license to use, reproduce, modify, prepare Derivatives, publicly
  display, publicly perform, and distribute the STG Works and Derivatives,
  subject to the obligations below.

Obligations
  1. Attribution: All copies and Derivatives must retain a clear notice:
     "Sovereign Titan Genesis — QUORUM‑STATE ‑INT'L" and reference to STG‑12L‑OS.
  2. ShareAlike: Any Derivative distributed in source or binary form must be
     licensed under STG‑12L‑OS or a compatible license that preserves the
     ethical and sovereign obligations herein.
  3. Source Availability: When distributing Derivatives in object or binary
     form, the distributor must make corresponding source code available under
     STG‑12L‑OS.
  4. No Central Dependency: Implementations must not require or enforce
     dependency on centralized surveillance, identity, or control services
     that undermine sovereignty.
  5. Export Compliance: Licensee must comply with applicable export and
     import laws.

B. STG‑12L‑CS — Commercial Sovereign Track (Paid, Contractual)
Grant of Rights
  The Licensor may, upon separate written agreement and payment of fees,
  grant commercial licenses that may include additional rights, warranties,
  indemnities, support, or proprietary modules not available under STG‑12L‑OS.

Commercial Terms (summary)
  1. Commercial License Agreement: Terms, fees, scope, and duration are set
     in a written contract between Licensor and Licensee.
  2. Confidentiality: Commercial agreements may include confidentiality and
     non‑disclosure obligations.
  3. Patent and IP: Licensor may grant patent licenses as negotiated in the
     commercial agreement.
  4. Support and SLA: Optional support, maintenance, and service level
     agreements are available under separate contract.

Common Provisions (both tracks)
1. Prohibited Uses
   The STG Works may NOT be used, adapted, or deployed for:
     a. Surveillance systems intended for mass monitoring without informed consent.
     b. Offensive weaponization, autonomous lethal systems, or direct harm.
     c. Exploitative commercial surveillance, targeted oppression, or human rights abuses.
     d. Any activity that intentionally circumvents privacy, civil liberties, or legal protections.
   If Licensee intends a use that may be ambiguous, Licensee must seek written
   permission from Licensor; Licensor reserves the right to deny permission.

2. Attribution and Notices
   All distributions must include this license text or a clear pointer to it,
   and retain copyright and attribution notices.

3. Patent and Trademark
   a. Patent: Licensor grants no patent license except as expressly provided.
   b. Defensive Termination: If Licensee initiates patent litigation against
      Licensor over STG Works, all rights granted to that Licensee terminate.
   c. Trademark: No rights to use Licensor trademarks are granted except by
      separate written permission.

4. Redistribution and Compatibility
   Derivatives under STG‑12L‑OS must remain under STG‑12L‑OS. Compatibility
   with other open licenses requires preservation of ethical and sovereignty clauses.

5. Termination
   Rights under this license terminate automatically upon material breach,
   including violation of Prohibited Uses or failure to comply with ShareAlike
   obligations. Termination does not affect obligations accrued prior to termination.

6. Disclaimer of Warranty
